                        "content": "The nurse has given suggestions to a client with trigeminal neuralgia about strategies to minimize episodes of pain. The nurse determines that the client needs further teaching if the client makes which statement?",
                        "subjectId": "ad5ab04c79144c0ea9b83385308c3b1d",
                        "difficultyIds": "a0f7d178f7b728b8bba7ef20ddeca62d",
                        "difficulty": "考试范围-Evaluating 评价",
                        "textAnalysis": "Rationale:\nFacial pain can be minimized by using cotton pads to wash the face and using room temperature water. The client needs to chew on the unaffected side of the mouth, eat a soft diet, and take in foods and beverages at room temperature. If brushing the teeth triggers pain, an oral rinse after meals may be helpful instead.",
                        "id": "d4c6e3e45c6744fdad13331910469943",
                        "mark": "0",
                        "collectionState": "0"
                    },
                    {
                        "optionList": [
                            {
                                "isRight": "0",
                                "userAnswer": "",
                                "isSelected": "0",
                                "id": "b1271b8b767d4f09b0414a6ff668f269",
                                "content": "It's a local reaction to nasal stuffiness."
                            },
                            {
                                "isRight": "0",
                                "userAnswer": "",
                                "isSelected": "0",
                                "id": "b956277dbb86413cb377e6a603e1ca4f",
                                "content": "It's due to a hypoglycemic effect on the cranial nerve."
                            },
                            {
                                "isRight": "0",
                                "userAnswer": "",
                                "isSelected": "0",
                                "id": "d982079b97ad4e28a52e7492ebb559cf",
                                "content": "Release of catecholamines with infection or stress leads to the pain."
                            },
                            {
                                "isRight": "1",
                                "userAnswer": "",
                                "isSelected": "0",
                                "id": "29856e5c01a046c69a4b23a6060cb5f4",
                                "content": "Pain is due to stimulation of the affected nerve by pressure and temperature."
